  "text": "where y µ are local coordinates on an emergent four-dimensional Riemannian manifold M. Thus the expansion of NC vector fields in D generates an infinite tower of the so-called polyvector fields [CITATION_1] . An interesting problem is to identify the theory described by the set of differential operators (2.10). Note that the leading term gives rise to the ordinary vector fields that will be identified with a frame basis associated to the tangent bundle T M of an emergent manifold M, as depicted in Fig. 1 . It is important to perceive that the realization of emergent geometry through the derivation algebra in Eq. (2.9) is intrinsically local [CITATION_2] . Therefore it is necessary to consider patching or gluing together the local constructions to form a set of global quantities. We will assume that local coordinate patches have been consistently glued together to yield global (poly)vector fields. Let us denote the globally defined vector fields by",
